        <p>
          Let <m>S = \{2,3,4,\ldots\}</m>.  How many ordered triples <m>(a,b,c)</m> are there in <m>S\times S \times S</m> such that <m>abc = 2 \cdot 3 \cdot 5 \cdot 7 \cdot 11 \cdot 13 \cdot 17</m>?
        </p>
      </statement>
    </exercise>

    <exercise>
